data.title: Small community library
data.text: As the main library for Lake Elsinore I was surprised how small this place was...although the kids section is probably as good as most cities this size. There's a single table with some computers in the middle of the one-room library and about ten aisles of books not counting the reference section. The small size also makes it intimate enough that conversations will be heard by all, as I noted the front desk never stopped talking to each other.
